Description: Sherd of shoulder of pottery amphora with tuen to body; one-piece amphora; painted band preserved at lower break; fine light red-brown clay without mica. Incised inscription.

Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Johnston 2006b / The Delta: From Gamma to Zeta (p.29 Table 1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.005)
